posts.name: Skye Leake
posts.cooked: In 2015, robot #1114 turned some heads (that year was pretty wild). Over the years, there have been various robots, including circular designs and octagon-shaped bots with unique features like bumper angles for navigating tight spaces during competitions. There have also been smaller, competition-ready robots and nonagon-based robots like Einstein, which had a perfect score rate. In 2022, robot #2481 impressed with its innovative frame setup for climbing challenges. Robots like #2383 and #4907 also stood out in recent years, though the fate of #1942 in 2023 remains unclear. Many lesser-known teams have created fascinating robots over the years.
